# Security

## Secrets
- Never hardcode credentials, API keys, or connection strings in source code.
- Load from environment variables, Keychain (Swift), or Databricks secret scopes.
- `.env` files for local development only. Never committed to source control.
- Rotate any secret that has been committed, even briefly.

## Input Validation
- Validate all user input at trust boundaries. Do not trust data from external sources.
- SQL: parameterized queries only. No f-string interpolation, no string concatenation.
- Pydantic `BaseModel` for data crossing trust boundaries (API input, config files, external data).
- Swift: validate `Codable` decoding results before use. Handle decoding failures explicitly.

## PHI / PII
- Never log PHI, PII, or credentials at any log level, including DEBUG.
- Error messages returned to users must not leak internal state, stack traces, or database details.
- Default to principle of least privilege for database connections and API scopes.
- Anonymize or hash identifiers in log output: `logger.info("processing", patient_hash=hash(pid))`.

## Pre-Commit Check
Before any commit, verify:
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets in the diff (`git diff` and `git diff --cached`)
- [ ] All user inputs validated at the boundary
- [ ] SQL uses parameterized queries, no string interpolation
- [ ] Error messages do not leak internals or sensitive data
- [ ] No PHI/PII in log statements
